ty's most powerful new medium. We encounter lesser-known essays by Béla Balázs, Walter Benjamin, and Siegfried Kracauer alongside interventions from the realms of aesthetics, education, industry, politics, science, and technology. The book also features programmatic writings from the Weimar avant-garde and from directors such as Fritz Lang and F.W. Murnau. Nearly all documents appear in English for the first time; each is meticulously introduced and annotated. The most comprehensive collection of German writings on film published to date, The Promise of Cinema is an essential resource for students and scholars of film and media, critical theory, and European culture and history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aFilm criticismxGermany. 0aFilm criticismzGermany. 0aFilm criticism. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryx20th centuryxGermany. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aBaer, Nicholas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCowan, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaes, Anton, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016z978311066754708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520962439423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520962439.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066754-7  UC Press eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyte